1.appengine.google.com
  create a project and copy the project Id written in small after you enter the name.

2.mirrorrr bslatkin github download
link :https://github.com/bslatkin/mirrorrr

3.google app engine sdk
  link : https://cloud.google.com/appengine/downloads

4.download python 2.7.8
link :https://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7.8/

6.install python and appengine sdk

5.open google appenginelauncher.exe Go to preferences in edit and enter different path variables.
 c:\python27\python.exe
 same for appengine  
6.in file option go to add existing project and add mirrorrr path

7.go to edit option in appengine and add project id at top as asked in application title.

8.click on deploy
 
9.click run
